  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Opening this issue to track audit and improvement for the next slot state cache\r\nWe suspect the next state slot cache has some issues given the `next_slot_cache_miss` count.\r\nWe also know specific issues exist, such that\r\n- It doesn't cache well in the event of a skip slot. 31-> one won't work because it's only cached up to 0. So we will still need to process 0->1. This can improve together with skip slot fcu call \r\n- There's only one entry, and it expects the subsequent retrieval to be based on the last processed block. This won't work with reorgs. We can improve upon from 1 entry to 2-3 entries  ",
